Cardio Good Fitness Project¶

(Case Study)

Description of Dataset:¶

Product - The model no. of the treadmill

Age - Age of the customer in no of years

Gender - Gender of the customer

Education - Education of the customer in no. of years

Marital Status - Marital status of the customer

Usage - Avg. # times the customer wants to use the treadmill every week

Fitness - Self rated fitness score of the customer (5 - very fit, 1 - very unfit)

Income - Income of the customer

Miles- Miles that a customer expects to run

4 Insights for Business¶

This Exploratory Data Analysis is on a dataset of 180 customers, using 3 Treadmill Products TM195,TM798 and TM498 and their profiles (based on Age, Gender, Education and Fitness Levels)

a) The Customer Ages ranges from 18 to 50, most of the customers are in age group 17-23 (Reference 2.a and 2.c)

b) Male Customers are majority in all age groups. (Reference 2.d)

c) Most customers have 16 years of education and income ranges of 40000 to 60000 (Reference 2.f and 2.g)

d) Majority of Customers use Treadmills 3 times a week, and have a fitness of 3/5 (Reference 2.i and 2.h)

e) Of the Products, TM195 is the most popular, followed by TM498 and TM798 (Reference 3.g)

f) Customers who owns TM798 has highest usage per week of around 4.6, other 2 models usage is around 3 times per week. And female customers use TM798 more than male. (Reference 3.h)

g) Higher Income customers have TM798 (Reference 3.h)

Recommendations:

a) Increase the sales of Treadmills to higher age groups, specifically 25-35 and 35-higher.

b) TM798 seems to be the most expensive Treadmill, as it is mostly used by higher income customers. A lower price may attract more customers.

c) To add more female customers, add more friendly features and increase the visibility of these products to this customer base.

d) Partnered Customers are a majority of customers, market the product line as a family friendly product.

e) Increase the awareness of fitness levels by adding features to monitor/tracking the usage and fitness levels.
